This paper is primarily focused on the design and analysis of data structures for approximate near neighbor search, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper uses techniques from hashing, probability theory, and data structures, which are all core topics in computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

However, the paper also discusses the use of locality-sensitive hashing in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications, which suggests that these sub-categories are also relevant. Additionally, the paper uses ideas from information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) to analyze the performance of the proposed data structure. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant.
